#: doc/en/get-started.md:212
msgid "### Representation formula (reprFormula)"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:214
msgid "By default, a Relation column displays the raw identifier of the linked record. You can define a **representation formula** in MoonScript to show a human-friendly label instead."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:216
msgid "- The syntax `@field` accesses fields of the linked record."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:217
msgid "- FK fields are resolved automatically: `@genre_id.libelle` follows the `genre_id` relation in the linked space and returns its `libelle`."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:218
msgid "- Multi-level chaining is supported: `@livre_id.genre_id.libelle` (copy → book → genre)."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:219
msgid "- If no formula is defined, the column uses the `_repr` field of the target space (if present), otherwise the raw id."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:221
msgid "**Examples:**"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:223
msgid "| Formula | Effect |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:224
msgid "|---------|-------|"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:225
msgid "| `@nom` | Shows the `nom` field of the linked record |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:226
msgid "| `@nom .. ' ' .. @prenom` | Concatenates last name and first name |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:227
msgid "| `@genre_id.libelle` | Follows the FK `genre_id` and displays the genre label |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:228
msgid "| `@livre_id.genre_id.libelle` | Chains two FKs (copy → book → genre) |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:230
msgid "**Concrete example — loans:**"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:232
msgid "In the `emprunts` space, the `exemplaire_id` column can display the title of the corresponding book by chaining FKs:"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:235
msgid "reprFormula : @livre_id.titre"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:238
msgid "(To show the book title for this copy.)"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/get-started.md:240
