#: doc/en/reference.md:114
msgid "## 2. Fields"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:116
msgid "A **field** is a column of a space. Each field has a type, a name, and may have a formula."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:118
msgid "### Available Types"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:120
msgid "| Type      | Description |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:121
msgid "|-----------|-------------|"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:122
msgid "| `String`  | String |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:123
msgid "| `Int`     | Integer |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:124
msgid "| `Float`   | Decimal number |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:125
msgid "| `Boolean` | Boolean (`true` / `false`) |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:126
msgid "| `UUID`    | Automatically generated UUID |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:127
msgid "| `Sequence`| Auto-increment integer (natural primary key) |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:128
msgid "| `Any`     | Free type (JSON) |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:129
msgid "| `Map`     | JSON object |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:130
msgid "| `Array`   | JSON array |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:131
msgid "| `Datetime`| Date and time |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:132
msgid "| `Relation`| Reference to a record in another space (display customizable via `reprFormula`) |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:134
msgid "### Computed Field (calculated column)"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:136
msgid "A computed field evaluates a **MoonScript expression** on each read. The value is **not stored**."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:138
msgid "The formula is the body of a function `(self, space) -> <formula>`. In MoonScript, `@field` is a shortcut for `self.field`:"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:140
msgid "**Example: `nom_complet` in `auteurs`** — combines first name, particle, and last name, handling null values:"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:150
msgid "### Trigger formula"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:152
msgid "A trigger formula is evaluated and its result **stored** on each creation or modification of the record (or only when listed fields in `triggerFields` change)."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:154
msgid "**Example: `cote_auto` in `livres`** — generates a bibliographic code from the first three letters of the title and the year (triggered on `titre` and `annee`):"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:163
msgid "### Formula languages"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:165
msgid "| Value        | Description |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:166
msgid "|--------------|-------------|"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:167
msgid "| `moonscript` | MoonScript (compiled → Lua on the fly) |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:168
msgid "| `lua`        | Native Lua |"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:170
msgid "### Helper `space` — access to other spaces"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:172
msgid "Formulas and triggers receive a second parameter `space` that allows access to all records of another space (full scan):"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:180
msgid "-- Get the label of a book's genre"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:181
msgid "next(g for g in *space(\"genres\") when g._id == @genre_id)?.libelle"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:184
msgid "`space(\"name\")` returns a Lua list of all records in the space `name`, each record being an object with `_id` (identifier) plus all data fields. Returns `{}` if the space does not exist."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:186
msgid "> **Note:** Full scan is suitable for small spaces (a few thousand records). For large volumes, prefer relations and aggregate widgets."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:188
msgid "### Reordering"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:190
msgid "Fields can be reordered by drag-and-drop (::) in the Fields panel."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:192
msgid "### Custom Relation Display (`reprFormula`)"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:194
msgid "For `Relation` type fields, `reprFormula` controls how the relationship is displayed"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:195
msgid "in the interface (grids, forms, etc.). The formula receives the linked record"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:196
msgid "as parameter (`self`) and must return a string."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:198
msgid "**Example:** For an `auteur_id` field pointing to the `auteurs` space:"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:201
msgid "# Display \"First Last\" instead of UUID"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:202
msgid "\"#{@nom} #{@prenom}\""
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:205
msgid "```lua"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:206
msgid "-- Equivalent Lua version"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:207
msgid "return self.nom .. \" \" .. self.prenom"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:210
msgid "### Field Type Conversion"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:212
msgid "The `changeFieldType` mutation allows converting a field from one type to another,"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:213
msgid "with an optional conversion formula to transform existing data."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:215
msgid "**Example:** Convert a `String` field to `Int`:"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:219 doc/en/reference.md:280
msgid "  changeFieldType(fieldId: \"...\", input: {"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:220 doc/en/reference.md:281
msgid "    fieldType: Int,"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:221 doc/en/reference.md:282
msgid "    conversionFormula: \"tonumber(self.amount)\","
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:222 doc/en/reference.md:263 doc/en/reference.md:283
msgid "    language: \"lua\""
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:223 doc/en/reference.md:284
msgid "  }) { id name fieldType }"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:227
msgid "If `conversionFormula` is omitted, values are automatically converted when possible,"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:228
msgid "or set to `null` otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:233
