#: doc/en/reference.md:352
msgid "### Display formula"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:354
msgid "A relation can have a **`reprFormula`** field: a MoonScript expression evaluated on each target record to produce a readable label."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:356
msgid "- The variable `self` (accessible via `@field`) is bound to the target record."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:357
msgid "- Examples: `@libelle`, `@nom .. ' ' .. @prenom`"
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:358
msgid "- FK fields are automatically resolved: `@genre_id.libelle` follows the `genre_id` relation and returns the `libelle` field of the corresponding genres record."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:359
msgid "- Chaining is possible over several levels: `@livre_id.genre_id.libelle` (exemplaire → livre → genre)."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:360
msgid "- When defined, FK columns in the grid display the formula result instead of the raw identifier."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:361
msgid "- In edit mode, a dropdown lists all target records with their computed label."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:362
msgid "- If no formula is defined, the column uses the `_repr` field of the target space (if it exists), otherwise the raw identifier."
msgstr ""

#: doc/en/reference.md:366
msgid "## 4. Data (records)"
msgstr ""

